comments.body:
Problem Statement:
The cursor in the TextInput component within the Composer loses its position when the user scrolls on Android devices.

Root Cause Analysis:
One potential cause is that the ScrollView containing the TextInput might be affecting the focus state of the input, or gesture handlers could be resetting the cursor position inadvertently.

Proposed Solution :
Here's an example of how I  might modify the ScrollView and gesture handling within the Composer component to address the issue:

jsx



import React, { useRef, useState } from 'react';
import { ScrollView, TextInput, View, Keyboard } from 'react-native';

// ... other imports and setup ...

function Composer(props) {
    // ... existing state and refs ...

    // Ref for the ScrollView
    const scrollViewRef = useRef(null);

    // Handler for when the TextInput is focused
    const handleInputFocus = () => {
        // Ensure the ScrollView doesn't scroll, which can disrupt the TextInput's focus
        if (scrollViewRef.current) {
            scrollViewRef.current.setNativeProps({ scrollEnabled: false });
        }
    };

    // Handler for when the TextInput loses focus
    const handleInputBlur = () => {
        // Re-enable scrolling when the TextInput is not focused
        if (scrollViewRef.current) {
            scrollViewRef.current.setNativeProps({ scrollEnabled: true });
        }
    };

    // ... other handlers and logic ...

    return (
        <ScrollView
            ref={scrollViewRef}
            keyboardShouldPersistTaps="handled"
            // ... other ScrollView props ...
        >
            <View>
                {/* ... other components ... */}
                <TextInput
                    // ... existing TextInput props ...
                    onFocus={handleInputFocus}
                    onBlur={handleInputBlur}
                />
                {/* ... other components ... */}
            </View>
        </ScrollView>
    );
}

// ... rest of the component, propTypes, defaultProps, etc. ...

export default Composer;
In this , the ScrollView has been given a ref so that its scrolling can be programmatically disabled when the TextInput is focused. This prevents the ScrollView from moving and potentially disrupting the cursor position. The keyboardShouldPersistTaps="handled" prop ensures that taps on the ScrollView when the keyboard is open do not dismiss the keyboard, which could also move the cursor.

Result:
With these changes, the TextInput should maintain its cursor position when the user interacts with other parts of the screen or when the ScrollView is touched. This solution assumes that the cursor issue is related to the ScrollView and gesture handling; if the problem persists, further investigation would be needed to identify other potential causes.
